    "short_description": "College town charm, craft beer, cat cafes, and great eats along one of the Midwest's best main streets.",
    "long_description": "Massachusetts Street in Lawrence, Kansas is one of the great walkable main streets in the Midwest — a lively, independent-spirited strip anchored by the University of Kansas that manages to feel both college-town casual and genuinely sophisticated. \n\nStart the morning at Global Cafe, a cozy brunch spot with a globally inspired menu and a relaxed, unhurried vibe. For coffee with a twist, Espurresso Cat Cafe pairs specialty drinks with resident adoptable cats in a charming storefront further up Mass St. Art lovers should carve out time for the Spencer Museum of Art on the KU campus — a free, world-class collection with rotating exhibitions and free validated parking. \n\nFree State Brewing Company is a Lawrence institution — the beloved original brewpub that helped define craft beer culture in Kansas, with house-brewed beers and a solid pub menu. For a more upscale dinner, Mass St. Fish House & Raw Bar delivers fresh oysters and refined seafood that stands apart in a college town setting. \n\nAfter dinner, John Brown's Underground is the place for a well-crafted cocktail in an intimate, moody atmosphere just off the main strip. Cap the evening — or sneak it in any time of day — with a scoop at Sylas and Maddy's Homemade Ice Cream, a Lawrence landmark scooping made-from-scratch flavors with a devoted local following.",
